event_name: International Sales Contacts Commercial Invoices and Other Doucments
description: Cost: $35, Pre-registration Required, International Sales Contacts Commercial Invoices and Other Documents: Avoiding legal pitfalls; Strategies on structuring your transactions; Documents and information you need and more, presented by MCLE

Corning Community College’s Small Business Development Center is offering the workshop “Understanding Incoterms” on Wednesday, June 18th from 9:00 – 11:30 a.m. at CCC's Academic & Workforce Development Center, 318 Madison Avenue, Room 004, Elmira, NY. This workshop is important for those currently involved with or thinking about exporting at some point in the future. Robert Stein of Mohawk Global Trade Advisors will help participants learn to decode the secret language of Incoterms 2010. The information covered will facilitate exporters in choosing the right code for international sales and purchasing contracts, selecting appropriate insurance requirements and applying the rules to domestic transactions. Registration is $20 and is required by June 16th. For more information or to register contact the SBDC at 607-937-6861 or sbdc@corning-cc.edu.

Take-Aways: •You will be aware of the new export security requirements for all exporters. •You will have an 11 point checklist to guide you to full compliance on every export. •You will have a better understanding of the regulations and specific tools & instructions on how to ensure you have a secure and compliant department & company.
Save the date! How Can I Export? Come find out. Multiple Presenters, Your Questions Answered, State Resources You Can Use to Sell Your Products Abroad.

The luncheon session will feature the SBA Small Business Awards, which pays tribute to small business owners and champions in 10 award categories. 8:15 a.m. Opening Session 9:15 a.m. General Session 10:30 a.m. Breakout Sessions 12:15 p.m. Small Business Awards & Closing Session Conference only: $35 Conference & Awards Luncheon: $65 To register by phone please call 213-580-7548.

Are you interested in getting new customers for your business, but don’t know where to begin? This seminar outlines the basic steps to exporting your product or service. Topics include: regulations such as licenses and permits; basic marketing concepts to help analyze the revenue potential; lending terminology; outline for a business plan and other resources to assist in getting new customers for your business by exporting. To register for this event, please click on LEARN MORE; or visit our website at www.mssbdc.org; or call in MS 1-800-725-7232. Pre-registration is recommended.

Take-Aways: •You will know the best type of L/C to use to manage your risk and exposure •You will know the specific strategies and tools to use during critical negotiations •You will be in the driver’s seat to properly structure your sales terms and financing options
